Originally, I planned to laser-cut the frame out of 4mm plywood or black acrylic, but after thinking about the structure I realized that cable management would be messy. I switched to 3D printing the frame so that I can integrate some sort of cable raceway inside the edge pieces / behind the LEDs. This will make the wiring easier, cleaner, and will reduce the complexity of the build.

